so, which ones?  If not, do you consider yourself<br>
atheist (there is no god) or agnostic (it is impossible<br>
to know, or I'm not sure, whether there is a god)?<br>
<br>
Me?  I've been an Evangelical Christian (my church<br>
is the Trinity Evangelical Free Church) since the age<br>
of 9, but lately I've been having some real problems<br>
accepting the fundamentalist doctrines of my faith.<br>
<br>
I also have a lot of questions that would make my<br>
pastor scream, like &quot;Did God commit suicide by allowing Himself to die when Jesus died on the cross, since Jesus is the same as God in the Christian faith?&quot;<br>
and &quot;If Jesus is God, did Jesus create the universe or<br>
did only God the Father create the universe?&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm USUALLY not one to accept anything blindly and<br>
without thinking it through first, especially religion.<br>
<br>
Love and cheers to all in your various EQ paths,<br>
