<br>
I agree that religion can be utilized (and most often is) as a tool to manipulate the masses and to justify heinous acts against nature and our fellow human beings.<br>
<br>
However, I believe that spirituality and/or belief in a higher power can be very fulfilling for certain individuals, and some teachings can lead people to contribute meaningfully to society.<br>
<br>
Although I do not choose to practice any traditional teachings, and consider myself to be agnostic at best, I would not go quite as far as to insult people who choose to believe in that which cannot be proven/disproven.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p><img src=http://webpages.marshall.edu/~parsons6/Tuppensig.jpg>
