Ever heard the expression &quot;Christianity would be great if it weren't for all those damn Christians&quot;?  That sums up my impression of most religions.  <br>
<br>
I think there's a lot of great stuff in most religions that would work towards making the world a great place to live in.  Too bad nobody pays attention to the spirit of their religious texts, and instead get bogged down in the literal nitty gritty, and act like fucking jerks.<br>
<br>
If I were to have some religious experience and grow faith again, I'd join the Episcopal Church (U.S. Branch).  It's close enough to Catholicism to feel comfortable, less most of the sexism &amp; homophobia.<br>
