<br>
I was raised Anglican Christian, but gradually applied logic and reason and have now reached the point where I tend to look at someone who thinks there's a big powerful person in the sky playing with our lives, about the same way as I would look at someone who genuinely thinks there's a little pink tooth fairy who skips around at night.  I firmly believe there is no god, no fate, no afterlife either good or bad, and no rhyme nor reason why things happen.  Consciousness is just a flicker of awareness in a complex brain, and when we die, we're gone forever as if we never existed.<br>
<br>
Possibly not the most comforting of beliefs, but logical, at least.  And all the more reason to enjoy and improve life in the here-and-now.<br>
