<br>
Me... <br>
well.. I -choose- to be Celtic Pagan.  For the most part, I believe the gods are nothing more than guides who have gone before.  Though... in exploring how Caillou feels about Tunare... I realised do believe in Danu, the eath mother, though as much more of a neutral than benevolent diety.  I have also done some exploration into Qabbalah and other meta-physical stuffs which in no-wise contradicts any other belief or conviction.  I am not a witch, I am not a druid, I am not even a priestess.  Nor do I wish to be.  I am jsut me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (I am also, intentionally, not a member of any coven or other group since the vast majority of organised religion sickens me and small groups can be jsut as bad or worse than large ones...).<br>
<br>
Oh... my parents think I am a satanist because I am not a christian.  One of the many points of contention between my parents and I.  I have had to threaten to block all communication from them to get my mother to stop -constantly- proslytising to me, and then it only stopped it for a little less than a year, but now it's a slow ignorable trickle.<br>
<br>
As for tolerance...don't tell me what to believe or how to believe it and I won't tell you the same.  I follow -my- path and will help someone to find their own... even back into a christian church.<br>
<br>
The amusing thing is that the person who helped me accept my path and accept this side of me was a practicing Roman Catholic.  He was the one to tell me it was okay to follow my inner self and get on the path that didn't hurt me at every turn (I had been -trying- to stay in the christian church out of deferance to my parents, but it was killing me inside since I dd not belong).<br>
<br>
Sorry for the ramble... I should have gotten some coffee an hour ago *laugh*.<br>
